\int_2^\infty{\dfrac{3x-2}{x^2(x-1)}}=1-\ln2
\dfrac{3x-2}{x^2(x-1)}=\dfrac{3x}{x^2(x-1)}-\dfrac{2}{x^2(x-1)}
\dfrac{3x}{x^2(x-1)}=\dfrac{3}{x(x-1)}=\ldots=-\dfrac{3}{x}+\dfrac{3}{x-1}
\dfrac{2}{x^2(x-1)}=\ldots=-\dfrac{2}{x^2}+\dfrac{2}{x-1}
A,B
C
\frac{3x-2}{x^2(x-1)}=\frac{Ax+B}{x^2}+\frac{C}{x-1}
\frac{Ax+B}{x^2}+\frac{C}{x-1}=\frac{(A+C)x^2+x(B-A)-B}{x^2(x-1)}
A+C=0, ~~B-A=3,~~-B=-2
\dfrac{3x-2}{x^2(x-1)}=\frac A{x^2}+\frac Bx+\frac C{x-1}
\implies 3x-2=A(x-1)+Bx(x-1)+Cx^2=(B+C)x^2+x(A-B)-A
A=2
x,A-B=3\implies B=A-3=-1
x^2,B+C=0\implies C=-B=1
  3x-2=A(x-1)+Bx(x-1)+Cx^2
x=1
C=3\cdot 1-2=1
x=0,-2=A(0-1)\implies A=2
x^2,B+C=0\implies B=-C=-1
